get.description:
Manage external call logs.

This view provides endpoints to retrieve, delete, and list call logs for external users.
A call log represents a record of a communication event, including details such as the agent involved,
the call ID, and the outcome of the call. This information is crucial for monitoring and evaluating
the performance of agents and the quality of interactions.

Required only when call_logs is all OR is number of first N calls. Only either of agent_id or assistant_id is required

parameters.name: agent_id
parameters.description: Filter by agent ID

parameters.name: assistant_id
parameters.description: Filter by assistant ID

parameters.name: call_ids
parameters.description: Comma-separated list of call log IDs (e.g., 1,2,3)

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: A page number within the paginated result set.

parameters.name: page_size
parameters.description: Number of results to return per page.

parameters.name: timestamp_from
parameters.description: Filter results from this timestamp (e.g. 2025-01-01T00:00:00Z)

parameters.name: timestamp_to
parameters.description: Filter results to this timestamp (e.g. 2025-01-31T23:59:59Z)

post.description:
Create a new call log entry.

This endpoint allows users to create a call log by providing necessary data in the request body.
Requires a valid API key in the headers.

Handle incoming Retell webhook requests.

This endpoint processes webhook requests from the Retell service, validates the request data,
and creates a call log entry based on the received data. Retell sends webhooks at the end of the call,
providing important information about the interaction.

Handle incoming VAPI webhook requests.

This endpoint processes webhook requests from the VAPI service, validates the API key,
and creates a call log entry based on the received data. VAPI sends webhooks at the end of the call,
providing important information about the interaction.
Create a new cron job for scheduled Evaluators execution
Handle Slack interactive component callbacks
